# Build-context ignore for repo-root builds.
#
# Currently only scout-notebook (helm/scout-notebook/Dockerfile) uses repo
# root as build context, so it can COPY sdk/python from above its own
# directory. Everything else builds from its own subproject context and is
# unaffected by this file.
#
# scout-notebook's Dockerfile only COPYs sdk/python; aggressive exclusion
# is safe.

# Local dev artifacts (node_modules can be hundreds of MB; build/ + caches
# slow context tar without contributing to the image)
**/node_modules
**/build
**/__pycache__
**/.pytest_cache
**/*.egg-info
**/dist
**/venv
**/.venv

# VCS + IDE
.git
.github
.idea
.vscode
.claude

# OS junk
**/.DS_Store

# Everything not relevant to scout-notebook's COPY of sdk/python
ansible
docs
tests
extractor
launchpad
analytics
helm/voila
helm/superset
helm/open-webui-bootstrap
helm/scout-dashboards
helm/hl7-transformer
helm/hl7log-extractor
helm/hive-metastore
keycloak
orchestrator
terraform
verify-node
zap
policy

# Markdown / configs at repo root that aren't needed in the image
*.md
LICENSE
renovate.json5
eslint.config.cjs
*.json
*.xml
readthedocs.yaml
